    <data name="Description_BackgroundStage" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>This field determines the background stage in the game. To quickly set it up, include "#meta stage [StringID]" in the chart comment (Replace [StringID] with the stage's ID or name).</value>
  </data>
    <data name="Description_BgmFile" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>To reduce the audio latency discrepancy between the game and Margrete, it is recommended to prioritize using .wav or .ogg audio files with a sample rate of 48000Hz.</value>
  </data>
    <data name="Description_BgmInitialBpm" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Specifies the starting BPM (Beats Per Minute) of the chart. It is used to calculate real offset.</value>
  </data>
    <data name="Description_BgmInitialTimeSignature" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Specifies the time signature (beats per bar and note value) at the start of the chart. It is used to calculate real offset.</value>
  </data>
    <data name="Description_DisplayBPM" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>BPM displayed in song selection menu</value>
  </data>
    <data name="Description_Genre" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>To quickly set it up, include "#meta genre [StringID]" in the chart comment (Replace [StringID] with the stage's ID or name).</value>
  </data>
    <data name="Description_InsertBlankMeasure" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Configure this through Margrete (Insert a blank bar before the first measure). If enabled, a silent measure with click cues is inserted at the beginning, ensuring that the first musical measure follows the blank.</value>
  </data>
    <data name="Description_MainDifficulty" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Used to specify which difficulty's chart property will be used as the base reference.</value>
  </data>
    <data name="Description_MainTil" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Configure this through Margrete (Base timeline). Determines which Timeline affects the bar line positions and AIR animation speed. Default is 0.</value>
  </data>
    <data name="Description_ManualOffset" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Configure this through Margrete. This value represents the offset (in seconds) applied to the song manually set by user. Positive values indicate a delay, while negative values indicate an advance.</value>
  </data>
    <data name="Description_RealOffset" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>This value represents the calculated offset (in seconds) applied to the song. Positive values indicate a delay, while negative values indicate an advance.</value>
  </data>
    <data name="Description_SongId" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The Song ID is extracted from Margrete's Song ID.</value>
  </data>
    <data name="Description_SortName" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Determines how songs are sorted in the game.</value>
  </data>
    <data name="Description_UnlockEventID" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The event that unlocks the "World's End" or "ULTIMA" chart in the game. If left blank, the generation of the associated Event.xml file will be skipped.</value>
  </data>
    <data name="Description_UnlockEventIDOption" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The event that unlocks the "World's End" or "ULTIMA" charts in the game.</value>
  </data>
    <data name="Description_ChartFileDiscovery" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Ordered chart formats to scan. Examples: [mgxc, ugc] or [ugc]. Earlier entries win when duplicate charts share the same Song ID and difficulty.</value>
